Description: Ostracon, fragment of the upper-body and neck of a grey-brown pottery jar, the fabric contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a brown-coloured slip, now much darkened, and faint traces of one line of black-painted hieratic text and traces of a circular impression.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amarna, el-, TA:30-31 U.25.7 I.45
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393623) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393623)
